    <header class="text-center py-5 bg-light border-bottom">
        <div class="container">
            <h1 class="fw-bold">Florida CTE AI Foundations</h1>
            <p class="text-muted">Instructional Design & Storyboard Development for Silimind</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <div class="container py-5" style="max-width: 950px;">
        <div class="row mb-4">
            <div class="col-12">
                <div class="confidential-note">
                    <strong>Note:</strong> This case study describes process, scope, and deliverables only. Source storyboard files, lesson copy, and final course assets are not displayed because the project contains client-owned instructional content.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row mb-5">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <h3 class="fw-bold">Problem</h3>
                <p>The client needed a high school AI Foundations module aligned to Florida CTE IT frameworks, but the existing prototype was not yet specific enough to support reliable implementation, quality assurance, or standards reporting. The project needed a complete storyboard that could bridge instructional intent, technical development, and DOE-aligned documentation.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <h3 class="fw-bold">Solution</h3>
                <p>I translated the initial Articulate Rise prototype into a full screen-by-screen storyboard specifying objectives, narrative flow, screen text, layouts, interactions, and assessment evidence. I also built a reusable alignment structure so each screen could be tied to benchmarks, checks for understanding, accessibility notes, and implementation guidance.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-center fw-bold mb-4">My Process</h2>
        <div class="row row-cols-2 row-cols-md-5 g-2 justify-content-center mb-5">
            <div class="col process-step"><strong>Analyze</strong><br>Standards</div>
            <div class="col process-step"><strong>Translate</strong><br>Prototype</div>
            <div class="col process-step"><strong>Design</strong><br>Storyboard</div>
            <div class="col process-step"><strong>Align</strong><br>Assessments</div>
            <div class="col process-step"><strong>Support</strong><br>Implementation</div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="fw-bold mb-4">Methodologies</h2>

        <div class="row align-items-start mb-5 methodology-copy">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <h4>Standards Alignment</h4>
                <p>I aligned lesson outcomes, instructional content, and assessment evidence to Florida CTE expectations so each screen served a measurable instructional purpose. This also made the course easier to review, revise, and hand off for implementation.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row align-items-start mb-5 methodology-copy">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <h4>Screen-by-Screen Storyboarding</h4>
                <p>I converted the original prototype into a detailed storyboard that specified learning objectives, screen text, interaction types, sequencing, assessment logic, and developer-facing notes. The goal was to remove ambiguity so the build could be implemented consistently and reviewed efficiently.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row align-items-start mb-5 methodology-copy">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <h4>Content Refinement</h4>
                <p>I rewrote explanations, examples, and prompts related to AI, data, and intelligent behavior so they were accurate, age-appropriate, and manageable for grades 9–12. This work focused especially on conceptual clarity, cognitive load, and consistency across the module.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row align-items-start mb-5 methodology-copy">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <h4>Collaboration & QA Support</h4>
                <p>I collaborated asynchronously with the client and a separate Storyline developer to clarify implementation details, resolve misinterpretations, and preserve instructional intent during the build phase. I also created a reusable alignment structure that supported QA review and future module development.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="fw-bold mb-4">Storyboard Table Schema</h2>
        <div class="schema-wrap mb-5">
            <div class="schema-header">
                <p class="schema-note"><strong>What is shown here:</strong> a redacted reconstruction of the storyboard table structure used in the project. The schema is authentic to the workflow, but the instructional copy has been abstracted to protect client-owned content.</p>
